decks.title: Java Interview Questions
decks.description: Advanced Java interview questions for experienced developers

questions.prompt: In Java, what is the primary difference between HashMap and ConcurrentHashMap?

choices.text: HashMap is synchronized, ConcurrentHashMap is not
ConcurrentHashMap allows concurrent modifications without external synchronization
HashMap supports null keys, ConcurrentHashMap does not
ConcurrentHashMap uses a single lock, HashMap uses multiple

questions.prompt: Which of the following are true about Java's volatile keyword? (Select all that apply)

choices.text: Prevents instruction reordering around the variable
Ensures visibility of changes across threads

questions.prompt: What happens when you override equals() but not hashCode() in a class used as a HashMap key?

choices.text: It works fine as long as equals() is consistent
The object may not be found in the HashMap

questions.prompt: In Spring Boot, what annotation is used to mark a method as a REST endpoint that handles HTTP GET requests?

choices.text: To ignore null values during serialization

questions.prompt: In Hibernate, what does the 'n+1 selects' problem refer to?

choices.text: Executing n+1 SQL queries instead of 1

questions.prompt: Which HTTP status codes indicate successful responses? (Select all that apply)

choices.text: The object it references is immutable

choices.text: When two threads compete for the same resource

choices.text: Flexible synchronization barrier for phases, like CyclicBarrier but reusable

choices.text: Controls access to resource with permit count
